sbhxx@ibm.net writes:

>Which is faster,  A WD 850 Meg HDD @ 10.5ms with cache memory or an IBM
>1 gig IDE drive at 8.6ms?

I cannot tell you which drive is faster, but access time is only a secondary
issue. The primary issue in harddrive speed is medium data transfer rate.
But data transfer speed depends on the overall system configuration, so it can
only be measured in a comparable way on similar systems. Look out for hard
drive tests in good magazines.
I would expect (from the experiences with their current SCSI drives) that the
IBM drive is faster. It is surely not a 'classical' IDE drive, since nearly 
all new drives support better PIO modes (2 or 3) and block reads, which make 
the difference in speed.

Regards,
Steffen 

