I actually have one of the old IBM 1G drives (part #70G8512) it is ATA-2 
(Rev. 0 dated 9.93) and does support PIO 3.

The new IBM Deskstar XP 1G has a bit slower 10.5 msec seek but the transfer 
rate is somewhat faster (probably due to using 2 disks instead of 3 as with
the older 1G, ie. higher bit density). It is ATA-2 Rev. 2e.

Both are 5400rpm and have 512k cache.

